          <h3>RN4CAST Lancet Study Redefines Global Nursing Policy</h3>
          <p>The RN4CAST consortium published findings in <em>The Lancet</em> demonstrating that each additional patient per nurse and a 10% increase in bachelor's-educated nurses were each independently associated with reduced patient mortality — compelling evidence that influenced workforce policy across Europe and beyond.</p>
          <span class="tl-tag">The Lancet · RN4CAST</span>
