          <p>As the COVID-19 pandemic exposed longstanding vulnerabilities in hospital nurse staffing and work environments, CHOPR researchers published rapidly on nurse burnout, staffing ratios, and workforce collapse — informing emergency policy responses and the national conversation on health system resilience.</p>
